iends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20years%20later%2C%20American%20consumers%20have%20mostly%20moved%20on%20from%20the%20pandemic%20and%20are%20spending%20more%20on%20experiences%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrioritizing%20experiences%2C%20however%2C%20has%20led%20to%20a%20major%20shift%20in%20their%20financial%20lives%3A%20The%20personal%20saving%20rate%20in%20the%20US%20has%20declined%20considerably.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20recently%20reported%20on%20how%20consumers%20in%20the%20US%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2024%2F03%2F29%2Fconsumer-spending-savings-yolo-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eembraced%20a%20sort%20of%20YOLO%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%26quot%3Byou%20only%20live%20once%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20mindset.%20In%202023%2C%20consumer%20spending%20on%20foreign%20trips%20and%20live%20entertainment%20rose%20by%20nearly%2030%20percent%2C%20according%20to%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpending%20levels%20have%20so%20far%20continued%20to%20rise%20in%202024%2C%20too.%20In%20February%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bea.gov%2Fnews%2F2024%2Fpersonal-income-and-outlays-february-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epersonal%20consumption%20expenditures%20increased%20by%20%24145.5%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%20January%2C%20with%20%24111.8%20billion%20spent%20on%20services%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20perhaps%20predictably%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bea.gov%2Fdata%2Fincome-saving%2Fpersonal-saving-rate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20US%20personal%20saving%20rate%20has%20declined%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20bureau.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20the%20personal%20saving%20rate%20was%203.6%20percent%2C%20a%20drop%20from%204.1%20percent%20the%20month%20before.%20(The%20rate%20sat%20at%204%20percent%20last%20November%20and%203.9%20percent%20in%2