20Equity%20Collaborative%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20offered%20advice%20to%20caregivers%20on%20navigating%20the%20role%20and%20addressing%20burnout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECwynar%20said%20stress%20is%20an%20unavoidable%20part%20of%20becoming%20a%20caregiver%2C%20but%20it's%20important%20for%20caregivers%20to%20acknowledge%20their%20emotions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECwynar%2C%20also%20an%20adjunct%20professor%20at%20Pennsylvania%20Western%20University%2C%20said%20stress%20can%20manifest%20for%20caregivers%20in%20various%20ways%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bphysical%20exhaustion%2C%20emotional%20strain%2C%20social%20isolation%2C%20and%20mental%20health%20challenges%20like%20anxiety%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20frustration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20emphasized%20that%20these%20feelings%20are%20normal%20and%20caregivers%20should%20give%20themselves%20room%20during%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAllow%20yourself%20to%20feel%20a%20range%20of%20emotions%20in%20response%20to%20the%20diagnosis%2C%20such%20as%20shock%2C%20sadness%2C%20anger%2C%20and%20fear%2C%26quot%3B%20Cwynar%20said.%20It's%20important%20to%20acknowledge%20and%20process%20these%20feelings%20in%20a%20healthy%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnchecked%20stress%20can%20lead%20to%20caregiver%20burnout%20that%20will%20negatively%20affect%20them%20and%20their%20loved%20ones%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22male%20care%20assistant%20with%20patient.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6608386d1caec1275a6b23e0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECaregivers%20can%20face%20burnout%20if%20stress%20goes%20unchecked.%20%3Cp%3EMaskot%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Cwynar%2C%20there's%20no%20specific%20time%20when%20caregiver%20burnout%20will%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can%20occur%20when%20caregivers%20experience%20prolonged%20stress%20and%20exhaustion%20from%20providing%20care%20to%20loved%20ones%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmotional%20distress%2C%20heightened%20irritability%2C%20anxiety%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20feelings%20of%20resentment%20can%20all%20go%20hand%20in%20hand%20with%20caregiver%20burnout.%20Cwynar%20added%20that%20weary%20caregivers%20can%20also%20experience%20sleep%20issues%2C%20changes%20in%20appetite%2C%20changes%20in%20weight%2C%20exhaustion%2C%20isolation%2C%20brain%20fog%2C%20and%20physical%20symptoms%20like%20hives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurnout%20can%20also%20surface%20when%20caregivers%20neglect%20their%20health%20and%20hygiene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSelf-care%20is%20essential%20for%20maintaining%20your%20well-being%20and%20resilience%20as%20a%20caregiver.%20By%20taking%20care%20of%20yourself%2C%20you%20are%20better%20equipped%20to%20provide%20effective%20care%20and%20support%20for%20your%20loved%20ones.%20You%20have%20to%20take%20care%20of%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20knows%20that%20can%20be%20easier%20said%20than%20done%20sometimes%20and%20might%20stir%20feelings%20of%20guilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRemember%20that%20caring%20for%20yourself%20is%20not%20selfish%2C%26quot%3B%20Cwynar%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20necessary%20for%20sustaining%20your%20caregiving%20role%20and%20overall%20well-being.%20Step%20away.%20Prioritize%20self-care%2C%20seek%20support%2C%20and%20be%20kind%20to%20yourself%20as%20you%20navigate%20the%20challenges%20of%20being%20a%20caregiver.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20are%20ways%20to%20minimize%20stress%2C%20including%20setting%20boundaries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Support%20Group%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660838f63f923f7dab02e705%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJoining%20a%20support%20group%20can%20help%20caregivers.%20%3Cp%3EDrazen%20Zigic%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECwynar%20said%20caregivers%20should%20set%20realistic%20expectations%20and%20recognize%20that%20they%20can't%20do%20everything%20perfectly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDelegate%20tasks%20when%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAsk%20for%20help%20when%20needed%20and%20focus%20on%20what%20is%20important%20for%20your%20loved%20ones'%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20it's%20good%20for%20caregivers%20to%20establish%20boundaries%20between%20their%20caregiver%20life%20and%20personal%20life.%20Joining%20a%20caregiver%20support%20group%20can%20also%20help%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20taking%20regularly%20scheduled%20breaks%20and%20exercising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20caregiver%20burnout%20is%20impacting%20your%20mental%20health%20or%20well-being%2C%20consider%20seeking%20therapy%20or%20counseling%20to%20address%20your%20emotional%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BRemember%20that%20taking%20care%20of%20yourself%20is%20essential%20to%20continue%20providing%20effective%20care%20to%20your%20loved%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-navigate-caregiver-burnout-after-relatives-cancer-diagnosis-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711817482000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6608212c16bde8d4ead3e362%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-navigate-caregiver-burnout-after-relatives-cancer-diagnosis-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Monica%20Cwynar%20is%20a%20full-time%20therapist%20but%20previously%20served%20as%20a%20hospice%20social%20worker%2C%20making%20her%20familiar%20with%20caregiver%20burnout%20and%20stress.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ledmonds%40businessinsider.com%20(Lauren%20Edmonds)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A45%2C%22canonic